Politician Rishad Amana, who joined ODM from DP, is on a quest to make Lamu an ODM stronghold. He plans to convince strong politicians to join the party and lock out the Jubilee Party.Amana is also leading a campaign to elect the next deputy governor from the Bajuni community in Lamu East. There, ODM enjoys massive support compared to Lamu West, which is largely Jubilee affiliated.Amana is also eyeing the Lamu West parliamentary seat. &ldquo;My job is to ensure ODM wins all seats in Lamu county. We are optimistic that will happen,&rdquo; he told the Star yesterday. Lamu has only two constituencies, Lamu East and Lamu West, whose MPs Athman Shariff and Julius Ndegwa have joined JP.